@page "/"

<PageTitle>Home</PageTitle>

<div class="container mt-5">

    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="text-center mb-5">
        <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold text-vave-heading">Hello, Vave 👋</h1>
        <p class="lead text-vave-body">
            Thank you for progressing me to this stage — I’m looking forward to meeting you on <strong>1st April</strong>.
        </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Intro Card -->
    <div class="card shadow-sm mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title text-vave-heading">About Project</h5>
            <p class="card-text text-vave-body">
                My name is <strong>Ryan Thomas</strong>. Please review the <strong>Rover Controller</strong> page using the navigation menu to explore the solution.
                <br />
                The UI is a Blazor WASM application, with a Web API backend. There is also a 'Core' DLL for shared models and a unit test project.
                <br />
                Due to time limitations there are defintitely areas for improvements, such as the 'RoverService' could be an Interface with Mocks for further unit testing. Playwright UI tests could also be created for the Blazor app.
                <br />
                As the scenario is open to some interuptations I have made it in a way where by you create a 'Rover' - this returns an ID and you can then execute commands on that. These are currently stored as JSON files in the API data folder.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Future Enhancements -->
    <div class="card shadow-sm">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title text-vave-heading">Future Enhancements</h5>
            <ul class="list-group list-group-flush mt-3 text-vave-body">
                <li class="list-group-item">
                    📍 Return the full path history to enable visualisation and animation of rover movement.
                </li>
                <li class="list-group-item">
                    ⚠️ Highlight invalid moves with clear visual feedback on the grid.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

</div>